.TH "rdma_find_gid_by_port" 9 "rdma_find_gid_by_port" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_find_gid_by_port \- Returns the GID entry attributes when it finds a valid GID entry for given search parameters. It searches for the specified GID value in the local software cache.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct ib_gid_attr *" rdma_find_gid_by_port
.BI "(struct ib_device *ib_dev "  ","
.BI "const union ib_gid *gid "  ","
.BI "enum ib_gid_type gid_type "  ","
.BI "u8 port "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *ndev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ib_dev" 12
The device to query.
.IP "gid" 12
The GID value to search for.
.IP "gid_type" 12
The GID type to search for.
.IP "port" 12
The port number of the device where the GID value should be searched.
.IP "ndev" 12
In RoCE, the net device of the device. NULL means ignore.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns sgid attributes if the GID is found with valid reference or
returns ERR_PTR for the error.
The caller must invoke \fBrdma_put_gid_attr\fP to release the reference.
